  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Cold Food Festival
  author: Lee Cham
  language: eng
  text: |-
    This year the Cold Food Festival finds me stranded in the capital.
    As seasons slip away like water, longing for home grows sharp.
    The willows trail their sorrows, swaying branches in the spring air,
    While silk trees dream of blooming after the rain has passed.

    Throughout the gardens, riders search for spring on horseback,
    And crows gather thick upon the fields where tombs receive their visitors.
    The world renews itself with each new color,
    Yet I grow old. Where shall I find the elixir to transform myself?
  footnotes:
    - The Cold Food Festival (寒食/한식) is observed two days before Qingming, traditionally a day for ancestral worship and tomb-visiting in East Asian cultures.
    - The 'elixir' (丹砂/단사) references the Daoist pursuit of immortality and spiritual transformation, suggesting the speaker's desire to transcend the constraints of aging and time.
